newdata = rownames_to_column(newdata, var = "name")
temp = rownames_to_column(data, var="name")
temp2 = select(temp,name, age, gender)

newdata = left_join(newdata, temp2, by="name")

gender_data = subset(newdata, subset = (gender==1 | gender==2))
gender_data$gender <- factor(gender_data$gender, levels=c(1,2), 
                       labels=c("male", "female"))

means = as.data.frame(fit.km$centers)
means$Cluster = row.names(means)

dfm = gather(means, key="Variable", value="Value",
              crim:medv)

ggplot(data=dfm, 
       aes(x=Variable, y=Value, group=Cluster,
           color=Cluster, shape=Cluster)) + 
  geom_point(size=3) +
  geom_line(size=1) +
  labs(title="Profiles for Neighborhood Clusters")

Neighborhood 1 is a rather “new” neighborhood, focused more on housing then employment. Neighborhood 2 is a high-crime, predominantly white neighborhood. Neighborhood 3 borders the Charles river, and is not significant in other regards. Most values are moderate. Neighborhood 4 has relatively low crime rates and moderate values for all other variables. Neighborhood 5 is a well connected, industrius neighborhood with relatively high property tax, and nitric oxide rates
